In [[Computer architecture|Computer Architecture]], While [[Branch prediction]]s Branch queue<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Sheikh|first=R.|last2=Tuck|first2=J.|last3=Rotenberg|first3=E.|date=2015-08-01|title=Control-Flow Decoupling: An Approach for Timely, Non-Speculative Branching|url=http://ieeexplore.ieee.org/document/6915862/|journal=IEEE Transactions on Computers|volume=64|issue=8|pages=2182–2203|doi=10.1109/TC.2014.2361526|issn=0018-9340}}</ref> takes place. When [[Branch predictor|Branch Predictor]] predicts if the branch is taken or not, Branch queue stores the predictions that to be used later.

Branch queue consists 2 values only. '''Taken''' or '''Not Taken'''.

Branch queue helps other algorithms to increase parallelism and optimization. It is not software implemented or Hardware one, It falls under hardware software co-design.

